text: MRT station for NUH. For NUS, you will need to walk a little or take bus. The station is quite deep and the escalator up is very long.

Drink already ready.. juat sit at it while making other things and make customer wait. Am the only customer at that time. Then came another customer, instead of giving the ready drink, she serve another customer. And never use hand glove while making drink. Her colleague using hand glove except for her.
Well connected to NUH and NUS via the medical blocks. The station has plenty of amenities for whoever needing a bite before heading further towards the buildings.

Good connectivity with NUH Main Building as well as Medical Centre. Spacious to handle the high traffic during peak hours, although when it gets really bad, even that isn't enough. On the main entrance side though, there is the large gantry for wheelchairs and strollers, but no elevator -.- , you have to head to the entrance at the other end of the station.
Good MRT Station to go to hospital
